  "Question": "<p>I'm getting confused between 2 variants of definition of induced matrix norm. Given a norm <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_268\"><math alttext=\"||\\cdot||\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mo>\u22c5</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> on <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_269\"><math alttext=\"\\mathbb{R}^{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>\u211d</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></semantics></math></span>, the induced matrix norm is defined by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_270\"><math alttext=\"\\left\\lVert A\\right\\rVert=\\max_{\\mathbf{v}\\not=0}\\frac{\\left\\lVert A\\mathbf{v}% \\right\\rVert}{\\left\\lVert\\mathbf{v}\\right\\rVert}\\qquad for\\quad A\\in\\mathbb{R}% ^{n\\times n}.\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo><mi>A</mi><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>max</mi><mrow><mi>\ud835\udc2f</mi><mo>\u2260</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\ud835\udc2f</mi></mrow><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo></mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo><mi>\ud835\udc2f</mi><mo fence=\"true\">\u2225</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\" separator=\"true\">\u2003\u2003</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>o</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\" separator=\"true\">\u2003</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>\u2208</mo><msup><mi>\u211d</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> </p> <p>I'm trying to deduce the second variant from this definition i.e. <span